{"uid":"a9e50076bf37266e","name":"test_outer_heredoc_is_quoted_so_remote_vars_dont_expand_locally","fullName":"tests.tasks.test_tasks_ssh_utils_scripts.TestSshTailscaleOnlyScript#test_outer_heredoc_is_quoted_so_remote_vars_dont_expand_locally","historyId":"28c85a32a59fb53961b39861a92c862d","time":{"start":1777452340493,"stop":1777452340493,"duration":0},"description":"``<<'DINARY_SSH_TS_EOF'`` (quoted delimiter) means the local\nshell leaves ``$TS_IP`` / ``$DROPIN`` literal while it ships\nthe script to the remote. Without the quotes both would\nexpand to the empty string *before* ``_ssh`` even base64-\nencodes the payload, which would end up silently writing a\nfile with ``ListenAddress :22`` (sshd rejects with a clear\nerror — but we would still have lost the pre-flight checks\nalong the way).\n","descriptionHtml":"<p><code>&lt;&lt;'DINARY_SSH_TS_EOF'</code> (quoted delimiter) means the local<br />\nshell leaves <code>$TS_IP</code> / <code>$DROPIN</code> literal while it ships<br />\nthe script to the remote. Without the quotes both would<br />\nexpand to the empty string <em>before</em> <code>_ssh</code> even base64-<br />\nencodes the payload, which would end up silently writing a<br />\nfile with <code>ListenAddress :22</code> (sshd rejects with a clear<br />\nerror — but we would still have lost the pre-flight checks<br />\nalong the way).</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[{"name":"_stub_socket_getfqdn","time":{"start":1777452329380,"stop":1777452329381,"duration":1},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"attachmentsCount":0,"stepsCount":0,"hasContent":false,"attachmentStep":false},{"name":"monkeypatch","time":{"start":1777452340491,"stop":1777452340491,"duration":0},"status":"passed","steps":[],"attachments":[],"parameters":[],"shouldDisplayMessage":false,"attachmentsCount":0,"stepsCount":